ifconfig - interface configuration, view and configure network interfaces, things like your IP address, MAC address, and whether a network interface is up or down.
iwconfig - wireless interface configuration, used to view or configure Wi-Fi interfaces
netstat - network statistics, shows network connections, routing tables, listening ports, and traffic stats.
ss - socket statistics, modern, faster replacement for netstat
dig - domain information groper, DNS lookup tool.
mousepad - lightweight graphical text editor, basically a simple notepad-style editor.
echo - prints text or variables to the terminal, commonly used in scripts or to display environment variables.
sudo apt search <keyword> - package search, searches available packages using a keyword in names and descriptions.
sudo apt search ufw - package search, looks for packages related to ufw in the repository.
sudo apt install <packagename> - package installation, downloads and installs the specified software package.
sudo apt remove <packagename> - package removal, uninstalls the package but keeps its configuration files.
sudo apt purge <packagename> - complete package removal, removes the package along with its configuration files.
sudo apt update - package list update, refreshes the local list of available packages from repositories.
sudo apt upgrade - system upgrade, upgrades all installed packages to their latest versions.


